The paper deals with robotic manipulation and machine learning algorithms to predict the success of candidate grasps. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the paper also uses computer vision techniques to evaluate grasp executions, which makes the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category a likely candidate as well. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms suggests that the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories are also possible. Finally, the paper deals with real-world experiments, which suggests that the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant.
